Mumbai: After imposing a ban on firecrackers during Diwali, the Chhattisgarh Environment Conservation Board (CECB) has disallowed bursting of crackers in six of its cities including the capital city of Raipur. The ban has  comes in to effect from December 1 and will continue till January 31. Besides Raipur, other cities where the ban has been imposed are Bilaspur, Bhilai, Durg, Raigarh and Korba. A statement issued by the State Environment Conservation Board said, the decision has been taken to control pollution which increases during winters due to the direction of wind.Also Read: India’s Firecracker Making Hub Sivakasi Sees 15% Drop In Business After SC Order To Ban Firecracker Sales In Delhi-NCR